item.description:
Multi-signatures enable multiple parties to jointly sign a common message with a compact signature, and are critical for scalable distributed systems. While pairing-free two-round constructions with key aggregation offer practical efficiency and deployability, achieving *tight security*—where the reduction loss is independent of the number of users or queries—remains challenging. T-Spoon (Crypto 2025) is the only prior tightly secure, pairing-free, two-round multi-signature supporting key aggregation, but its signatures are large (9 field elements + 2 group elements). This work introduces **Earpick**, a family of tightly secure schemes in the standard discrete logarithm setting:  
- **Earpick-MS**, a multi-signature scheme with signatures of just **3 field elements + 1 bit**, reducing size by ≈3.5× over T-Spoon;  
- **Earpick-TS**, the first tightly secure, pairing-free, *two-round threshold signature*—improving upon prior three-round tight constructions (Chen, PKC 2025; Bacho & Wagner, CiC 2026);  
- **Earpick-muMS**, extending tight security to the multi-user setting without enlarging signatures.  
All schemes support key aggregation and eliminate non-tight reductions via novel challenge-response design and optimized random oracle modeling.
